title: Global energy commodity price index 2013 to 2030
yAxis: Price index in real 2010 U.S. dollars
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Price index in real 2010 U.S. dollars. In total the number of data points it has is 12.
In general Price index in real 2010 U.S. dollars has fallen over the Year.

Price index in real 2010 U.S. dollars is roughly constant from 2013 to 2014, gradually decreasing from 2014 to 2015, slightly increasing from 2015 to 2018, roughly constant from 2018 to 2025, and finally roughly increasing from 2025 to 2030.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2014 and 2015.
The highest Price index in real 2010 U.S. dollars, of value 120.1 was reached at Year 2013
The lowest Price index in real 2010 U.S. dollars, of value 55.1 was reported at Year 2016
